summary: An Ordinance accepting certain deeds to the City of Seattle for the extension of 47th Avenue Southwest, from The Fauntleroy Land Company, a Washington corporation, executed on the 16th day of July, 1920, from the J. M. Colman Company, a Washington corporation, executed on the 14th day of July, 1920, and from H. Johnson and Judith Johnson, his wife, executed on the 16th day of July, 1920, and laying off and establishing 47th Avenue Southwest.
